The paper focuses on developing generative probabilistic models for two specific tasks related to tables with an entity focus. These tasks involve populating rows with additional instances (entities) and populating columns with new headings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, as it deals with developing smart assistance capabilities for spreadsheet programs. Additionally, the paper also considers a knowledge base and a large table corpus for estimating the components of the models, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its methods using experimental simulations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
